  "text": "In a previous study [CITATION_1] , the mean annual increase in UPDRS-III scores was 3.3 points. This study hypothesized that the mean (SD) difference in UPDRS-III scores between the bottom two-thirds and the top one-third of subjects sorted by baseline CRP concentrations would be 1.0 (2.0) point. Assuming a power of 90% and P<0.05, the sample size was estimated to be 192 patients.",
